      "content": "but camus is just being optimistic because he has to be. like, \"creating beauty\" feels so small when you realize how fleeting it is. the scale of it just makes every single emotion and effort feel hollow. it’s like trying to paint a masterpiece on a canvas that’s already being incinerated. why bother trying to find \"purpose\" in a system that's fundamentally broken and temporary?",
