    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "resistance feels like a lot of unnecessary work though. if the end result is always zero, then the \"effort\" of living is just a way to prolong the inevitable discomfort. wouldn't it be more logical to just accept the nothingness now? like, if the outcome is predetermined to be nothing, why force yourself to endure the struggle of the middle part? it seems like just a delay of the inevitable.",
